 103 Distress.-

190212
1It shall be lawful for any official of the Board to whom a warrant issued under section 101 is addressed to distrain, wherever it may be found in the cantonment, any movable property of or standing timber, growing crops or grass belonging to the person therein named as defaulter, subject to the following conditions, exceptions and exemption, namely:- 

1389042
athe following property shall not be distrained-

359783
ithe necessary wearing apparel and bedding of the defaulter or of his wife or of his children;



606025
